NEFSC Bottom Trawl Data

survey.Rd

DATASET_DESCRIPTION

survey

Format

A data frame with 3937953 rows and 27 variables:

CRUISE6

character Cruise ID

STATION

character Station ID

STRATUM

character Stratum

TOW

character Tow ID

SVSPP

character Northeast Resource Surveys Species code

CATCHSEX

character Species-specific numeric sex code

SVVESSEL

character Vessel ID

YEAR

double Year

SEASON

character Season

LAT

double Latitude

LON

double Longitude

EST_TOWDATE

double Date with estimated time

DEPTH

double Depth

SURFTEMP

double Surface water temperature

SURFSALIN

double Surface salinity

BOTTEMP

double Bottom water temperature

BOTSALIN

double Bottom salinity

ABUNDANCE

double Abundance (number of fish caught on a single tow; redundant for rows with the same CRUISE6, STATION, and TOW)

BIOMASS

double Biomass (biomass caught on a single tow; redundant for rows with the same SVSPP, CRUISE6, STATION, and TOW)

LENGTH

double Length

NUMLEN

double Number of fish at the specified length (redundant for rows with the same SVSPP, CRUISE6, STATION, TOW, and LENGTH)

Species

character Species common name

spst

character Species and strata

stock_area

character Stock region

Region

character Stock region

date

character Date

fish_id

character Unique fish ID

Source

Oracle query of svdbs using the survdat package.

Details

  • Function call: survdat::get_survdat_data(channel = channel, filterByYear = NA, all.season = TRUE, shg.check = T, conversion.factor = T, use.SAD = F, getBio = FALSE, getLengths = T)
